<h3></h3>
<div class='layout'><p>16 Officers</p><p>第16章 警官</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>RAYCH--……According to Hari Seldon,……original meeting with Raych……entirely accidental. He……simply a gutter urchin from whom Seldon……asked directions.……his life, from that moment……continued to be intertwined with that of……great mathematician until ...</p><p>芮奇：……根据哈里·谢顿的说法，最初与芮奇相遇纯属偶然。他只是个贫民区的顽童，而谢顿只是向他问路。但从那一刻起，他的人生就和那位大数学家纠缠在一起，直到……</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>ENCYCLOPEDIA GALACTICA</p><p>——《银河百科全书》</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The next morning, dressed from……waist down, having washed……shaved, Seldon knocked on……door that……to Dorss adjoining room……said in a moderate voice, "Open……door, Dors."</p><p>第二天早上，谢顿刚刚梳洗完毕，腰部以上还完全赤裸，就敲着通往隔壁铎丝房间的那扇门，以适度的音量说：“开门，铎丝。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>She did.……short reddish-gold curls of……hair were still……and……too……dressed only from……waist down.</p><p>她照做了。她满头金里透红的鬈曲短发还湿淋淋的，而且上身同样完全赤裸。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon stepped back in embarrassed alarm. Dors looked down at……swell of……breasts indifferently……wrapped a towel around……head. "What is it?"……asked.</p><p>谢顿尴尬万分地向后退去。铎丝毫不在意地低头看了看鼓胀的乳房，再把一条毛巾裹在头上。“什么事？”她问。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon said, looking……to……right, "I……going to……you about Wye."</p><p>谢顿将头偏向右侧，说道：“我正要向你请教卫荷。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors said very naturally, "About……in connection with what?……for goodness sake, don't make me talk to your ear. Surely, youre……a virgin."</p><p>铎丝非常自然地说：“为何怎么样？看在老天的份上，别让我对着你的耳朵说话。不用说，你当然不是处男。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon said in a hurt tone, "I……merely trying to be polite. If……don't mind, I certainly dont.……its……why about what.……asking about……Wye Sector."</p><p>谢顿以感伤的语调说：“我只是试图保持礼数。只要你不在意，我当然也不会。我说的不是为何怎么样，我是在问你有关卫荷区的事。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Why do……want to know?……if……prefer:……Wye?"</p><p>“你为何想知道？或者你喜欢这么说：为何问卫荷？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Look, Dors,……serious. Every once in a while,……Wye Sector is mentioned--the Mayor of Wye, actually. Hummin mentioned him,……did, Davan did. I don't know anything about either……sector or……Mayor."</p><p>“听好，铎丝，我很认真。每隔一阵子，就会有人提起卫荷区——事实上，是提到那个卫荷区长。夫铭提到过他，你提到过，达凡也提到过。我却对这个区和这个区长都一无所知。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I'm……a native Trantorian either, Hari. I know very little,……youre welcome to what I do know.……is near……south pole--quite large, very populous--"</p><p>“哈里，我也不是土生土长的川陀人。我知道得非常少，不过欢迎你分享我所知道的一切。卫荷接近南极——面积相当大，人口非常多……”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Very populous at……south pole?"</p><p>“在南极还能人口非常多？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Were……on Helicon, Hari. Or on Cinna either. This is Trantor. Everything is underground……underground at……poles or underground at……equator is pretty much……same. Of course, I imagine they keep their day-night arrangements rather extreme--long days in their summer, long nights in their winter--almost as it would be on……surface.……extremes……just affectation; theyre proud of being polar."</p><p>“哈里，我们不是在赫利肯，也不是在锡纳上。这里是川陀，万事万物都在地底，而两极的地底和赤道的地底可说差不多。当然，我猜想他们有着相当极端的昼夜分布——夏天的白昼很长，冬天则刚好相反，几乎和地表的情形一样。这种极端纯属矫揉造作，其实他们是以身居极地自豪。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"But Upperside they must be cold, indeed."</p><p>“可是他们的上方一定真的很冷。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Oh yes.……Wye Upperside is snow……ice,……it doesnt……as thickly there as……might think. If it did, it might crush……dome,……it doesnt……that is……basic reason……Wyes power."</p><p>“喔，没错。卫荷的上方冰雪交加，可是冰雪堆积得不如你想象中那么厚。果真如此的话，就可能会压垮穹顶，但事实则不然，这正是卫荷握有大权的基本原因。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>She turned to……mirror, removed……towel from……head,……threw……dry-net over……hair, which, in a matter of five seconds, gave it a pleasant sheen.……said, "You have no idea……glad I am……to be wearing a skincap," as……put on……upper portion of……clothing.</p><p>她转身面向镜子，将毛巾从头上取下，再将“干发网”罩在头上。不过五秒钟，她的头发便呈现悦人的光泽。她一面说：“你难以想象我多庆幸摆脱了人皮帽。”一面套上了衣服。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"What……the……layer to do with Wyes power?"</p><p>“冰层和卫荷的权力有什么关系？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Think about……Forty billion people……a great deal of power……every calorie of it eventually degenerates into heat……has to be gotten……of.……piped to……poles, particularly to……south pole, which is……more developed of……two,……is discharged into space. It [melts] most of……ice in……process……I'm sure that accounts……Trantors clouds……rains, no matter……much……meteorology boggins insist that things……more complicated than that."</p><p>“想想看，四百亿居民每天消耗大量能源，每一卡的能量最终都会退化成热量，而且必须设法排除。这些热量全被输送到两极，尤其是开发得较好的南极，然后排放到太空去。在这个过程中，它融化了大部分的冰。我确定这正是川陀上空云雨的来源，不论那些气象学究如何坚决主张实际情形并没那么简单。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Does……make……of……power before discharging it?"</p><p>“在将这些热量排放之前，卫荷有没有加以利用？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"They may,……all I know. I haven't……slightest idea, by……way, as to……technology involved in discharging……heat,……I'm talking about political power. If Dahl were to stop producing usable energy, that would certainly inconvenience Trantor,……there……other sectors that produce energy……can up their production and, of course, there is stored energy in……form or another. Eventually, Dahl would have to be dealt with,……there would be time. Wye, on……other hand--"</p><p>“据我所知，他们也许有。顺便告诉你，关于排放热量的科技，我连最粗浅的概念都没有，但我所说的是政治上的权力。假如达尔停止生产可用的能源，当然会使整个川陀感到不便，可是还有其他生产能源的行政区，它们可以提高产量。此外，当然，还有种种的储备能源可以救急。达尔的问题终究得解决，不过总有缓冲时间。反之，卫荷……”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Yes?"</p><p>“怎么样？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Well,……gets……of at least 90 percent of……the heat developed on Trantor……there is no substitute. If……were to shut down……heat emission,……temperature would start going up……over Trantor."</p><p>“嗯，川陀所产生的各种热量，至少百分之九十由卫荷负责排放，没有任何替代管道。假如卫荷将热量发射全部关闭，整个川陀的温度便会开始上升。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"In……too."</p><p>“卫荷本身也会。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"[Yes],……since……is at……south pole, it……arrange an influx of cold air. It wouldnt do much good,……Wye would last longer than……rest of Trantor.……point……then, that……is a very touchy problem……the Emperor……the Mayor of……is--or at least……be--extremely powerful."</p><p>“啊，可是既然卫荷位于南极，它就能设法导入冷空气。这并不会有太大的作用，但卫荷会比川陀其他各处撑得更久。所以结论是，对皇帝而言，卫荷是一个非常棘手的问题，而卫荷区长是——至少可以是极有权力的人。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"And what kind of a person is……present Mayor of Wye?"</p><p>“现任卫荷区长又是个什么样的人？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"That I don't know. What……occasionally heard would make it seem that he is very……and pretty much a recluse,……hard as a hypership hull……still cleverly maneuvering……power."</p><p>“这点我不知道。根据我偶尔听来的传闻，他似乎非常老迈，而且几乎是个隐士，但他和超空间飞船一样刚硬，而且仍在用高明的手段谋取权力。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Why, I wonder? If……that old, he couldnt hold……power……long."</p><p>“为什么？我不明白，既然他那么老了，就不能再掌握多久的权力。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Who knows, Hari? A lifelong obsession, I suppose. Or else……the game……the maneuvering……power, without……real longing……the power itself. Probably if he……the power……took over Demerzels place or even……Imperial throne itself, he would feel disappointed because……game would be over. Of course he might, if he……still alive, begin……subsequent game of keeping power, which might be just as difficult……just as satisfying."</p><p>“哈里，谁晓得呢？一种终生的沉迷吧，我这么想。或者它是个游戏……只是为了谋取权力，并非真正渴求权力的本质。假如他夺权成功，取代了丹莫刺尔的位置，甚至自己登上皇位，说不定他反而会感到失望，因为这场游戏就结束了。当然啦，倘若那时他还活着，他或许会开始下一个游戏，那就是固守权力。这也许和前一个游戏同样困难，因而同样会带来成就感。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon shook……head.……strikes me that no……could possibly want to be Emperor."</p><p>谢顿摇了摇头。“这使我有一种感想，不可能有人想要当皇帝。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"No sane person would, I [free],……the Imperial wish, as it is frequently called, is like a disease that, when caught, drives……sanity.……the closer……get to high office,……more likely……are to catch……disease. With each ensuing promotion--"</p><p>“我同意，有理智的人都不会。但是这种所谓的‘皇帝梦’就像一种疾病，一旦染上就会使人丧失理智。而愈接近高位，就愈有可能染上这种疾病。随着一次又一次的晋升……”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"The disease grows still more acute. Yes, I……see that.……it also seems to me that Trantor is so huge a world, so interlocking in……needs……so conflicting in……ambitions, that it makes up……major part of……inability of……Emperor to rule.……doesnt he just leave Trantor……establish himself on some simpler world?"</p><p>“这种疾病就会变得更急性。没错，这点我明白。但我还有另一个感想，川陀是如此庞大的一个世界，众人的需求是如此牵一发动全身，众人的野心是如此冲突不断，使它成为皇帝治下最大的不稳定因素。他为何不干脆离开川陀，迁都到某个较单纯的世界呢？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors laughed. "You wouldnt……that if……knew your history. Trantor is……Empire through thousands of years of custom. An Emperor……is……at……Imperial Palace is……the Emperor. He is a place, even more than a person." </p><p>铎丝哈哈大笑。“倘若你了解历史，就不会问这个问题。根据上万年的惯例，川陀就等于帝国。一个皇帝若不在皇宫中，他就不算是个皇帝。皇帝不像是一个人，反而比较像一个地方。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon sank into silence,……face rigid,……after a while Dors asked, "Whats……matter, Hari?"</p><p>谢顿陷入沉默，面孔也变得刚硬。过了一会儿，铎丝问道：“哈里，怎么回事？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I'm thinking," he said in a muffled voice. "Ever since……told me that hand-on-thigh story,……had fugitive thoughts that--Now your remark about……Emperor being a place rather than a person seems to have struck a chord."</p><p>“我在寻思。”他以含糊的声音说，“自从你告诉我那个毛手毛脚的故事之后，我就有一种飘忽的想法。现在你又提到皇帝比较像个地方，而不像一个人，似乎刚好起了共鸣。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"What kind of chord?"</p><p>“什么样的共鸣？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon shook……head. "I'm still thinking. I……be……wrong."……glance at Dors sharpened,……eyes coming into focus.……any case, we ought to go down……have breakfast. Were late……I don't think Mistress Tisalver is in a good enough humor to have it brought in……us."</p><p>谢顿摇了摇头。“我仍在寻思，或许我全搞错了。”他瞥向铎丝的目光转趋尖锐，他的视线则重新聚焦。“无论如何，我们该下去吃早餐了。我们已经晚啦，我想堤沙佛夫人可没有那么好的心情，会帮我们把早餐端进来。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"You optimist," said Dors.……own feeling is that shes……in a good enough humor to want us to stay--breakfast or not.……wants us……of here."</p><p>“你是个乐天派。”铎丝说，“我自己的感觉是，她没有那么好的心情，会想让我们留下来——不论有没有早餐。她想要让我们离开这里。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"That……be,……were paying her."</p><p>“或许如此，但我们让她有钱可赚。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Yes,……I suspect……hates us enough by……to scorn……credits."</p><p>“没错，但我怀疑她现在恨我们入骨，根本不屑赚我们的信用点。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Perhaps……husband Will feel a……more affectionate concerning……rent."</p><p>“她的丈夫也许会对房租比较难分难舍一点。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"If he……a single word to say, Hari,……only person……would be more surprised than me to hear it would be Mistress Tisalver.--Very well,……ready."</p><p>“他若有任何意见，哈里，恐怕只有堤沙佛夫人会比我更惊讶了。很好，我准备好了。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>And they moved down……stairs to……Tisalver portion of……apartment to find……lady in question waiting……them with less than breakfast--and with considerably more too.</p><p>于是他们走下楼梯，来到堤沙佛一家在这栋公寓的活动范围，发现两人所讨论的那位女士正等在那里——没有准备早餐，但准备了一个更大的惊奇。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Casilia Tisalver stood ramrod straight with a tight smile on……round face……her dark eyes glinting.……husband……leaning moodily against……wall. In……center of……room were……men……were standing stiffly upright, as though they……noticed……cushions on……floor……scorned them. </p><p>凯西莉娅·堤沙佛硬邦邦地直直站在那里，一张圆脸带着僵硬的笑容，一双黑眼珠闪闪发光。她的丈夫则闷闷不乐地倚在墙边。房间正中央还有两个人，也都直挺挺地站着，仿佛他们早已注意到地板上的坐垫，只是不屑坐在上面。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Both……the dark crisp hair……the chick black mustache to be expected of Dahlites. Both were thin……both were dressed in dark clothes so nearly alike that they were surely uniforms. There……thin white piping up……over……shoulders……down……sides of……tubular trouser legs. Each had, on……right side of……chest, a rather dI'm Spaceship-and-Sun,……symbol of……Galactic Empire on every inhabited world of……Galaxy, with, in this case, a dark……in……center of……sun.</p><p>这两个人都有一头鬈曲的黑发，以及达尔人必备的粗黑八字胡。两人皆很瘦小，皆穿着一套深色服装。那两件衣服极其相似，想当然是一种制服，上面绣着细白的滚边，上至肩头，下至管状裤腿的外侧。他们的右胸处挂着一个不甚明显的“星舰与太阳”徽章，在银河系每一个住人世界上，它所代表的都是银河帝国。只不过眼前这个徽章，太阳中央还有一个深色的“达”字。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon realized immediately that these were……members of……Dahlite security forces.</p><p>谢顿立刻了解，这两个人是达尔维安警察的成员。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Whats……this?" said Seldon sternly.</p><p>“这是怎么回事？”谢顿以严厉的口气说。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>One of……men stepped forward. "I am Sector Officer Lanel Russ. This is my partner, Gebore Astinwald."</p><p>其中一人向前走来。“我是本区巡官拉涅尔·鲁斯。这是我的搭档，葛柏·艾斯汀伍德。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Both presented glittering identification holo-tabs. Seldon didnt bother looking at them. "What it is……want?"</p><p>两人都出示了亮晶晶的全息标签识别证。谢顿根本懒得看，只是问道：“你们想干什么？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Russ said calmly, "Are……Hari Seldon of Helicon?"</p><p>鲁斯以平静的口气说：“你是来自赫利肯的哈里·谢顿吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I am."</p><p>“是的。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"And……you Dors Venabili of Cinna, Mistress?"</p><p>“而你是来自锡纳的铎丝·凡纳比里吗，夫人？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I am," said Dors.</p><p>“是的。”铎丝答道。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I'm here to investigate a complaint that……Hari Seldon instigated a riot yesterday."</p><p>“我来这里是要调查一件投诉，昨天有个哈里·谢顿煽起一桩暴动。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I……no such thing," said Seldon.</p><p>“我没做那种事。”谢顿说。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Our information is," said Russ, looking at……screen of a small computer pad, "that……accused a newsman of being an Imperial agent, thus instigating a riot against him."</p><p>“我们的情报指出，”鲁斯看了看一个小型电脑板的屏幕，“你指控一名记者是帝国特务，因此煽起一场暴动对付他。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors said,……was I……said he……an Imperial agent, Officer. I……reason to think he was. It is surely no crime to express ones opinion.……Empire……freedom of speech."</p><p>铎丝道：“说他是帝国特务的人是我，警官，我有理由这样想。表达一个人的意见当然没有罪，帝国是有言论自由的。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"That does……cover an opinion deliberately advanced in order to instigate a riot."</p><p>“并不包括为了煽起一场暴动，而蓄意提出的意见。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"How……you……it was, Officer?"</p><p>“警官，你怎能这样说？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>At this point, Mistress Tisalver interposed in a shrill voice, "I……say……Officer.……saw there……a crowd present, a crowd of gutter people……were just looking……trouble.……deliberately said he……an Imperial agent when……knew nothing of……sort……she shouted it to……crowd to stir them……It……plain that……knew what……was doing."</p><p>这时，堤沙佛夫人以尖锐的声音插嘴道：“警官，我能这样说。当时她看到外面有一群人，一群从贫民区来的人，他们只是想找麻烦。她故意说他是帝国特务，其实她根本毫无概念，但她就这样对群众喊话，把他们煽动起来。事实很明显，她知道自己在做什么。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Casilia," said……husband pleadingly,……she cast……look at……and he said no more.</p><p>“凯西莉娅。”她的丈夫以恳求的语气呼唤她，但挨了一个白眼之后，他就什么也不说了。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Russ turned to Mistress Tisalver. "Did……lodge……complaint, Mistress?"</p><p>鲁斯转向堤沙佛夫人。“夫人，是你投诉的吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Yes. These……have been living here……a……days……theyve done nothing……make trouble. Theyve invited people of……reputation into my apartment, damaging my standing with my neighbors."</p><p>“是的。这两个人在这里住了好几天，除了惹麻烦什么也不干。他们邀请低级民众进我的公寓，破坏我在邻居心目中的地位。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Is it against……law, Officer," asked Seldon,……invite clean, quiet citizens of Dahl into ones room?……two rooms upstairs……our rooms. We have rented them……they……paid for. Is it a crime to speak to Dahlites in Dahl, Officer?"</p><p>“邀请清洁而平和的达尔公民进某人的房间，”谢顿问道，“警官，难道是违法的行为吗？楼上两个房间是我们的，我们已经租下，并且付了房租。警官，在达尔境内和达尔人交谈也犯法吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"No, it is not," said Russ. "That is……part of……complaint. What gave……reason, Mistress Venabili, to suppose……person……so accused was, in fact, an Imperial agent?"</p><p>“不，不犯法。”鲁斯说，“那并非投诉的一部分。你究竟有什么理由，凡纳比里夫人，认为你指控的那个人确实是帝国特务？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors said,……had a small brown mustache, from which I concluded he……not a Dahlite. I surmised he……an Imperial agent."</p><p>铎丝说：“他只有两小撇棕色胡须，我据此断定他不是达尔人。我进而推测，他是一名帝国特务。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"You surmised? Your associate, Master Seldon,……no mustache at all. Do……surmise he is an Imperial agent?"</p><p>“你推测？你的同伴，谢顿老爷，他根本没有胡子。你也推测他是一名帝国特务吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"In……case," said Seldon hastily, "there……no riot. We asked……crowd to take no action against……supposed newsman……I'm sure they didnt."</p><p>“无论如何，”谢顿急忙道，“根本没有暴动。我们要求群众别对那个所谓的记者采取任何行动，我确定他们听进去了。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Youre sure, Master Seldon?" said Russ. "Our information is that……left immediately after making your accusation.……could……witness what happened after……left?"</p><p>“你确定，谢顿老爷？”鲁斯说，“根据我们的情报，你们做出指控后立刻离去。而你离去后，又怎能见证发生了什么事？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I couldnt," said Seldon, "but……me……you--Is……man dead? Is……man hurt?"</p><p>“我不能，”谢顿说，“可是让我问你——那人死了吗？那人受伤了吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"The……has been interviewed. He denies he is an Imperial agent……we have no information that he……He also claims he……handled roughly."</p><p>“那人曾接受约谈。他否认自己是帝国特务，我们也没有情报显示这点。他还声称曾遭到虐待。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"He……well be lying in both respects," said Seldon. "I would suggest a Psychic Probe."</p><p>“他很可能这两件事都撒了谎。”谢顿说，“我建议使用心灵探测器。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"That cannot be done on……victI'm of a crime," said Russ. "The sector government is very firm on that. It might do if……two, as……criminals in this case, each underwent a Psychic Probe. Would……like us to do that?"</p><p>“不能对受害者那样做，”鲁斯说，“区政府对这点非常坚持。倒是有可能让你们两人——这件案子中的罪犯——接受一次心灵探测。你们希望我们那样做吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon……Dors exchanged glances……a moment, then Seldon said, "No, of course not."</p><p>谢顿与铎丝交换了一下眼色，然后谢顿说：“不，当然不要。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Of course not, repeated Russ with just a tinge of sarcasm in……voice, "but youre ready enough to suggest it……someone else." </p><p>“当然不要，”鲁斯重复道，声音中仅有些许嘲讽之意，“但你却毫不犹豫地建议对别人这样做。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The other officer, Astinwald,……had so……not said a word, smiled at this. </p><p>另外一位警官（艾斯汀伍德）目前为止尚未说半句话，此时则露出微笑。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Russ said,……also have information that……days……you engaged in a knife fight in Billibotton……badly hurt a Dahlite citizen named"--he struck a button on……computer……and studied……new page on……screen--"Elgin Marron."</p><p>鲁斯又说：“我们还有情报显示，昨天你们曾在脐眼进行一场械斗，而且重伤一名达尔公民，名叫——”他按下电脑板的一个按键，看了看屏幕上的新画面。“厄金·玛隆。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors said, "Does your information tell……how……fight started?"</p><p>铎丝问：“你的情报有没有告诉你械斗的起因？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"That is irrelevant at……moment, Mistress. Do……deny that……fight took place?"</p><p>“夫人，那和目前的讨论无关。你否认发生过那场械斗吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Of course we don't deny……fight took place," said Seldon hotly, "but we deny that we in……way instigated that. We were attacked. Mistress Venabili……seized by this Marron……it……clear he……attempting to rape her. What happened afterward……pure self-defense. Or does Dahl condone rape?"</p><p>“我们当然不否认发生过械斗，”谢顿激动地说，“但我们坚决否认是我们挑起来的。当时我们遭到攻击！那个玛隆抓住了凡纳比里夫人，而且显然企图性侵她。接下来发生的事，只是单纯的自卫行动。难道达尔纵容强奸吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Russ said with very little intonation in……voice, "You……you were attacked? By……many?"</p><p>鲁斯以近乎平板的声音说：“你说你们遭到攻击？被多少人攻击？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Ten men."</p><p>“十名男子。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"And……alone--with a woman--defended yourself against……men?"</p><p>“而你只有一个人，再加上一个女的，对抗这十名男子？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Mistress Venabili……I defended ourselves. Yes."</p><p>“是的，只有我和凡纳比里夫人两人御敌。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"How is……then, that neither of……shows……damage whatever?……either of……cut or bruised where it doesnt show right now?"</p><p>“那么，你们两人怎么没有显露任何伤痕？你们有没有谁被割伤或打伤，只是受伤的部位现在看不到？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"No, Officer."</p><p>“没有，警官。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"How is……then, that in……fight of one--plus a woman--against ten,……are in no……hurt,……that……complainant, Elgin Marron,……been hospitalized with wounds……Will require a skin transplant on……upper lip?"</p><p>“那么，在一个人——再加一个女的——对付十人的格斗中，你们怎么会毫发无损？而那个原告，厄金·玛隆，却伤痕累累地躺在医院，而且上唇需要接受皮肤移植？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"We fought well," said Seldon grimly.</p><p>“我们身手很好。”谢顿绷着脸说。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Unbelievably well. What would……say if I told……that three……have testified that……and your friend attacked Marron, unprovoked?"</p><p>“好得难以置信。假如我告诉你已经有三个人作证，说你和你的朋友在毫无挑衅的情况下攻击玛隆，你会怎么说？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I would……that it belies belief that we should.……sure that Marron……a record as a brawler……knifeman. I tell……that there were……there. Obviously,……refused to swear to a lie. Do……other three explain……they……not come to……help of their friend if they witnessed……under unprovoked attack……in danger of……life? It must be clear to……that they……lying."</p><p>“我会说没有人相信我们会那样做。我确定那个玛隆有案可查，是个滋事分子和带刀的凶徒。我告诉你当时共有十个人，显然，其中有六个拒绝为谎言宣誓作证。请问其他三人有没有做出解释，为何他们未曾出手帮助他们的朋友——倘若他们果真目睹他遭到毫无来由的攻击，而且性命受到威胁？你一定很清楚他们是在说谎。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Do……suggest a Psychic Probe……them?"</p><p>“你建议对他们施用心灵探测器吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Yes.……before……ask, I still refuse to consider……for us."</p><p>“是的。而且你不用再问了，我仍然拒绝用在我们身上。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Russ said,……have also received information that yesterday, after leaving……scene of……riot,……consulted with……Davan, a known subversive……is wanted by……security police. Is that true?"</p><p>鲁斯说：“此外我们还接到情报，说你们昨天离开暴动现场后，曾经去会晤一个名叫达凡的人，一个公认的、被维安警察通缉在案的颠覆分子。这是真的吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Youll have to prove that without help from us," said Seldon. "Were……answering……further questions."</p><p>“这点你得自己证明，我们不会帮你的忙。”谢顿说，“我们不准备再回答任何问题。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Russ……away……pad. "I'm afraid I must……you to come with us to headquarters……further interrogation."</p><p>鲁斯将电脑板收起来。“恐怕我必须请两位跟我们回总部，去接受进一步的侦讯。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I don't think thats necessary, Officer," said Seldon.……are Outworlders……have done nothing criminal. We have tried to avoid a newsman……was annoying us unduly, we tried to protect ourselves against rape……possible murder in a part of……sector known……criminal behavior,……weve spoken to various Dahlites. We……nothing there to warrant……further questioning. It would come under……heading of harassment."</p><p>“我认为没这个必要，警官。”谢顿说，“我们是外星人士，况且并未做出任何犯罪行为。我们曾经试图回避一名记者，因为他过分骚扰我们。而在本区中以犯罪闻名的地带，我们曾经试图保护自己，避免遭到性侵和可能的杀害。此外，就是我们和许多达尔人谈过话。我看不出有任何理由该对我们做进一步的盘问，这样做等于是一种骚扰。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"We make these decisions," said Russ. "Not you. Will……please come with us?"</p><p>“作决定的是我们，”鲁斯说，“不是你。请两位跟我们走好吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"No, we Will not," said Dors.</p><p>“不，我们不去。”铎丝说。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Watch out!" cried……Mistress Tisalver. "Shes……two knives."</p><p>“小心！”堤沙佛夫人叫道，“她有两把刀子。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Officer Russ sighed……said, "Thank you, Mistress,……I know……does." He turned to Dors.……you know……a serious crime to carry a knife without a permit in this sector? Do……have a permit?"</p><p>鲁斯警官叹了一声。“谢谢你，夫人，不过我早就知道了。”他又转向铎丝，“你可知道在本区，未经许可携带刀械是一项重罪？你有许可证吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"No, Officer, I dont."</p><p>“我没有。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"It……clearly with an illegal knife, then, that……assaulted Marron? Do……realize that that greatly increases……seriousness of……crime?"</p><p>“那么，你用来攻击玛隆的武器，显然是一把非法刀械？你可了解这是严重的罪上加罪？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"It……no crime, Officer," said Dors. "Understand that. Marron……a knife as well……no permit, I am certain."</p><p>“警官，这不算什么罪。”铎丝说，“请你了解一件事，玛隆也有一把刀，而且我确定他也没许可证。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"We have no evidence to that effect……while Marron……knife wounds, neither of……have any."</p><p>“这点我们并无证据，不过玛隆身上有刀伤，你们两人却谁也没有。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Of course he……a knife, Officer. If……don't know that every……in Billibotton……most……elsewhere in Dahl carry knives……which they probably don't have permits, then youre……only……in Dahl……doesnt know. There……shops here wherever……turn that sell knives openly. don't……know that?"</p><p>“警官，他当然有一把刀。假使你不知道脐眼每一个人，以及达尔区大部分的人都随身带刀，而且或许都没有许可证，那你就是唯一不知情的达尔人。在此地不论你转到哪里，都能找到公然贩刀的商店。这点你不知道吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Russ said,……doesnt matter what I know or don't know in this respect.……does it matter whether other people……breaking……law or……many of them……All that matters at this moment is that Mistress Venabili is breaking……anti-knife law. I must……you to give up those knives to me right now, Mistress,……the……of……must then accompany me to headquarters."</p><p>鲁斯说：“我对这方面知道得多或少并不重要，其他人是否违法或有多少人违法也不重要。此时此刻，重要的是凡纳比里夫人触犯了《反刀械法》。夫人，我必须请你立刻将那两把刀交给我，然后你们两人必须随我到总部去。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors said,……that case, take my knives away from me."</p><p>铎丝说：“既然这样，把我的刀子取走啊。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Russ sighed. "You must……think, Mistress, that knives……all……weapons there……in Dahl or that I need engage……in a knife fight. Both my partner……I have blasters that Will destroy……in a moment, before……can drop your hands to your knife hilt--however fast……are. We wont……a blaster, of course, because we……not here to kill you. However, each of us also……a neuronic whip, which we……use on……freely. I hope……wont……for a demonstration. It wont kill you, do……permanent harm of……kind, or leave……marks--but……pain is excruciating. My partner is holding a neuronic whip on……right now.……here is mine.--Now,……us have your knives, Mistress Venabili."</p><p>鲁斯又叹了一声。“夫人，你该不会认为刀械是我们达尔唯一的武器，或是我需要和你进行一场刀战吧。我和我的搭档都有手铳，可以在瞬间将你摧毁，远在你的双手能碰到刀柄之前——不论你有多快。当然，我们不至于使用手铳，因为我们不是来杀你的。然而，我们每个人还有一柄神经鞭，可以随意用来对付你。我希望你不会要求一次示范。它不会要你的命或是造成任何永久性伤害，甚至不会留下任何伤痕——但那种痛苦却是难以忍受的。现在我的搭档正举着神经鞭对着你，而这把则是我的——好啦，凡纳比里夫人，把你的刀交给我们。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>There……a moments pause……then Seldon said, "Its no use, Dors. Give……your knives."</p><p>顿了一下之后，谢顿说：“没有用的，铎丝，把刀子给他吧。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>And at that moment, a frantic pounding sounded at……door……they……heard a voice raised in high-pitched expostulation.</p><p>就在这个时候，大门响起一阵狂暴的敲击声，大家也都听到一个拉高音调的吼叫。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Raych……not entirely left……neighborhood after he……walked them back to their apartment house.</p><p>芮奇带他们回到公寓后，并未真正离开这个社区。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He……eaten well while waiting……the interview with Davan to be done……later……slept a……after finding a bathroom that more or less worked. He really……no place to go……that……that……done. He……a home of sorts……a mother……was……likely to be perturbed if he stayed away……a while.……never was.</p><p>在达凡住处外等待的时候，他曾经饱餐了一顿。后来，在找到一间勉强还能使用的厕所后，他又小睡了一会儿。现在这些事都已经做完了，他实在没什么地方可去。他也算有个家，但他即使好一阵子不回去，他的母亲也不大可能担心——她从未担心过。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He……not know……his father……and wondered sometimes if he really……one. He……been told he……to have……and……reasons……that……been explained to……crudely enough. Sometimes he wondered if he ought to believe so peculiar a story,……he……find……details titillating. </p><p>他不知道生父是谁，有时甚至怀疑自己是否真有父亲。不过有人曾经告诉他，说他的父亲一定存在，并以很露骨的方式将理由解释给他听。他有时也会怀疑是否该相信这么奇特的故事，但他的确发觉那些细节令人心痒。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He thought of that in connection with……lady.……was an……lady, of course,……she……pretty……she could fight like a man--better than a man. It filled……with vague notions.</p><p>他将那件事和那位大姐联想到一块。她当然是个年纪不小的大姐，可是她相当漂亮，而且能像男人一样打斗——甚至比男人更厉害。这使他心中充斥着一些模糊的想法。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>And……had offered to……him take a bath. He could swI'm in……Billibotton pool sometimes when he……some credits he didnt need……anything else or when he could sneak……Those were……only times he……wet……over,……it……chilly……he……to wait to……dry.</p><p>而且，她曾提出要让他洗个澡。他偶尔也能在脐眼的游泳池泡一泡，那是当他有些没处花的信用点，或是能偷溜进去的时候。游泳是他唯一全身浸湿的机会，但总是相当寒冷，而且事后还得把身子晾干。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Taking a bath……different. There would be……water, soap, towels,……warm air. He wasnt sure what it would feel like, except that it would be nice if……was there.</p><p>洗澡则是完全不同的一回事，会有热水、肥皂、毛巾与热气流。他不确定那会是什么样的感觉，只晓得她若在场必将十分美好。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He……walkway-wise enough to know of places where he could park himself in an alley……a walkway that would be near a bathroom……still be near enough to where……was,……where he probably wouldnt be found……made to……away. </p><p>他对这一带的人行道足够熟悉，晓得人行道旁巷道内的哪些地方可容他藏身，不但离一间厕所不远，又能和她的距离仍然够近，而且或许不会被人发现，不至于落荒而逃。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He spent……night thinking strange thoughts. What if he……learn to read……write? Could he do something with that? He wasnt sure what,……maybe they could tell him. He……vague ideas of being paid money to do things he didnt know……to do now,……he didnt know what those things might……He would have to be told,……how do……get told?</p><p>他整夜都在想一些奇怪的念头。他若是真的学会读书写字，那会怎么样？他能用这本事做什么事吗？他不确定能做什么，但她或许能告诉他。他有些模糊的概念，知道做些现在还不会做的事可以赚到工资，却不晓得那会是些什么样的事。得有人告诉他才行，但要怎样才能找到这样的人？</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>If he stayed with……man……the lady, they might help.……why should they want……to stay with them?</p><p>假如他留在那个男人和那位大姐身边，他们或许会帮助他。可是，他们怎么会要他留在身边呢？</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He drowsed off, coming to later,……because……light……brightening,……because……sharp ears caught……heightening……deepening of sounds from……walkway as……activities of……day began.</p><p>他打起瞌睡，不久又清醒过来，并非由于光线变得明亮，而是他敏锐的听力察觉到来自人行道的声音越来越嘈杂，标志着一天的活动已经开始。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He……learned to identify almost every variety of sound, because in……underground maze of Billibotton, if……wanted to survive with even a minimum of comfort,……had to be aware of things before……saw them.……there……something about……sound of a ground-car motor that he……heard that signaled danger to him. It……an official sound, a hostile sound……</p><p>他早已学会分辨几乎每一种声音，因为在脐眼那种地底迷宫中，即使只是想要苟活，也必须在看到任何事物之前便先行察觉。他现在听到的是地面车发动机的声音，而他听出了其中的危险讯息。它具有一种官方的声音，一种敌意的声音……</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He shook himself awake……stole quietly toward……walkway. He scarcely needed to……the Spaceship-and-Sun on……ground-car.……lines were enough. He knew they……to be coming……the……and……lady because they……seen Davan. He……not pause to question……thoughts or to analyze them. He……off on a run, beating……way through……gathering life of……day. </p><p>他甩了甩头，让自己清醒过来，再悄悄向人行道走去。他几乎不需要看到那辆地面车的“星舰与太阳”徽章，光看车子的外型就足够了。他知道，他们必定是来抓那一男一女的，因为他俩见到了达凡。他并未停下来质疑自己的想法或加以分析，而是立刻拔腿飞奔，在逐渐拥挤的人群中冲出一条路。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He……back in less than fifteen minutes.……ground-car……still there……there were curious……cautious onlookers gazing at it from……sides……from a respectful distance. There would soon be more. He pounded……way up……stairs, trying to remember which door he should bang……No time……the elevator. </p><p>他在十五分钟内又回来了。那辆地面车还在那里，许多好奇而谨慎的民众从四面八方望过来，但都维持着一段不短的距离。想必旁观者很快会越来越多。他一面“砰砰砰”地爬着楼梯，一面努力回想该捶哪家的门。他根本来不及搭升降机。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He found……door--at least he thought he did--and he banged, shouting in a squeak, "Lady! Lady!"</p><p>他终于找到那扇门，至少他认为没错。他开始使劲捶门，同时以尖锐的声音喊道：“大姐！大姐！”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He……too excited to remember……name,……he remembered part of……mans. "Hari!" he shouted. "Let me in."</p><p>由于过度激动，他竟然忘了她的姓名，不过他还记得那男子的名字。“哈里！”他吼道，“让我进去。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The door opened……he rushed in--tried to rush……The rough hand of an officer seized……arm. "Hold……kid. Where do……think youre going?"</p><p>房门打开后，他立刻冲进去——应该说是试图冲进去。一名警官的粗大手掌抓住了他的手臂。“慢着，小子，你以为这是哪里？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Leggo! I aint done nothin." He looked about. "Hey, lady, whatre they doin?"</p><p>“撒手！我啥也没做。”他四下望了望，“嘿，大姐，他们在干啥？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Arresting us," said Dors grimly.</p><p>“逮捕我们。”铎丝绷着脸说。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"What for?" said Raych, panting……struggling. "Hey, leggo,……Sunbadger. don't go with him, lady.……don't have to go with him."</p><p>“为什么？”芮奇一面喘气一面挣扎，“嘿，撒手，你这个徽子。别跟他走，大姐，你不必跟他走。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"You……out," said Russ, shaking……boy vehemently.</p><p>“你滚开。”鲁斯一面说，一面猛力摇晃这个男孩。</p></div>
